title: Roomies
description: When Vicki doesn't get the apartment she was suppose to get, she needs a place to stay. And the only one who can take her is Cassie and she reluctantly does. But she cramps Cassie's style.

title: Fallen Idol
description: Vicki'a father comes for a visit but things change when she catches him with Nancy.

title: Super-Mom
description: Jan's daughter wants to take up ballet and Jan doesn't want to disappoint her. But she can't afford it on her waitress salary alone. So she does a little moonlighting. But when it affects her job, the girls tell her that it's ok to say no to her daughter. But Jan is determined not to fail her.

title: Up on the Roof
description: When there's a fire in the building and because the restaurant is on the top, it's difficult for them to get out. And among the people is a man who's on a date with someone who is not his wife and an elderly couple who are celebrating their anniversary. When an evacuation plan is implemented, the staff have to go last.

title: Making the Grade
description: Jan decides to go out with one of her teachers just as her course is ending. But when she decides to break it off, she learns that her final grade could be in jeopardy because he doesn't want to end it. So she turns to the Dean who tells her it's her word against his and that she should tell him to just accept it.

title: You're Not Old, You're Fired
description: The girls are told that Nancy is being retired and that Lois is replacing her. Lois eventually learns that Nancy was retired because the boss thought she's too old. So they go to Nancy to tell her that and they find her working as a waitress in a diner.

title: Boys of Summer
description: A baseball team who is in town for a series of games is having their meals at the restaurant. And the girls make connections with a different player.

title: Of Mace and Men
description: After Maggie is mugged, the girls decide to start carrying mace.

title: The Wedding
description: A wedding is going to take place at the restaurant. And Cassie knows the groom. And when he sees her, he wants to leave his fiancée to be with her.

title: Her Back to the Future
description: As the staff prepares for a wedding reception, Nancy dozes off and has a bizarre dream about her own marriage, ten years in the future to Sonny.

title: Killing of Sister Dot
description: Dot is thrilled about her new part on a soap opera until she realizes her character is in imminent danger of being killed off.

title: The Date Show
description: Nancy has just the solution to Howard's mid-life crisis: she invites him to a square dance, and she won't take no for an answer.

title: Search and Strike
description: Nancy is having a bad week: hotel management wants her to search the waitresses' lockers, and Howard wants her to back off.

title: The Vegas Show: Part 2
description: When a jealous Howard follows Nancy to Las Vegas, he's horrified to find her gambling at a blackjack table with a lounge lizard named Chick.

title: A Pen Pal for Your Thoughts
Twelve Angry Women
description: Sonny manages to infuriate an entire table of feminists while Dot starts dating one of Amy's ex-boyfriends.

title: Skin Deep
description: After seeing Howard flirting with a much younger woman, Nancy begins considering having a face lift.

title: Take Back Your Mink
description: Richie hits the big money which lands Jan in a mink coat. However, is his sudden success short lived?

title: The One About the Tattooed Lady
Daddy's Little Girl
description: Jan has hopes of reuniting her divorced parents but there is one hitch in her plan, her father is newly engaged.

title: Ginger and the Senator
description: Ginger's efforts to campaign for her favorite senator make front-page news when she's photographed sitting on his lap.

title: Healings, Nothing More Than Healings
description: Sonny becomes an instant hero after saving a choking victim by administering the Heimlich maneuver. Meanwhile, Nancy and Howard contemplate taking separate vacations.

title: A Very Scary It's a Living
He Never Sang for His Father
The Dark at the Top of the Top
A Very Special It's a Living
